reviews.headline: Irritated my face
reviews.comments: I really liked the texture of this foundation, but it had a strong scent of chemicals and it irritated my face. My face looked like it had patches of chemical burns on it that turned a dark red and got hot. I settled on.a foundation shade, but there wasn't one that was perfect my undertone. The warm colors leaned very yellow. I ended up returning the foundation because of what it did to my face. I was able to recover, but it was pretty bad and had me worried for a bit.

reviews.headline: My Go To Foundation
reviews.comments: Weightless Skin Foundation SPF15  is my new favorite foundation! It's so lightweight I forget I'm wearing makeup.  Blends easily and tones down all my surface redness.  The color blends so well I don't get any makeup lines.

reviews.headline: Almost perfect
reviews.comments: I really like this foundation. The color is perfect for me and it looks and feels great, plus I like the fact that it has sunscreen in it. One star off because the salesperson said it was definitely full coverage and it is not.

reviews.headline: Absolutely
reviews.comments: It gives you a beautiful glow and spreads on so easily. It's not heavy, just gives you a thin layer of color. Great for people who use a little foundation

reviews.headline: I would keep buying this product
reviews.comments: Medium Coverage, but I like it

reviews.headline: Just wow
reviews.comments: Best foundation I've ever wore. It lays so so perfecf on the skin, i just love it! Its pricey, but after wearing a few times I understand why. I also have bb face base moisturizer and maybe thats why its giving such a nice look. Definitely recommend buying!

reviews.headline: Melted off my face
reviews.comments: I got a sample and tried it then went to a soccer game. Outside for 10 minutes at the game and this was streaking  down my face. It  melted completely off, along with the rest of my face makeup. Absolutely do not recommend.

reviews.headline: Best foundation on the market
reviews.comments: Okay, yall.  I don't particularly like writing reviews, but sometimes it needs to be done.  I will say that this foundation has and always, and will always be my go to. With that being said, i do take issue with thr amount of product that it comes with.  I feel like im going through it too fast, & i dont even use if daily. But I absolutely love the formula. It doesnt oxidize and leave an orange ring on your jaw line, which is key.  It blends perfectly. It matches perfectly, it stays on forever, and I've never had an issue with it transferring on my clothes, which is huge for me.  Ive tried to find other foundations that are on the cheaper side, but always come back to this.  If you use bobbi "face base" before applying, its absolute perfection.   Again, its the amount of product that im getting that i take issue with.  Especially for the price.  But im hooked.  I highly highly recommended

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I finally broke down and bought this foundation after hearing about it abd wanting to for years.  I was disappointed the color mstch is horrible and i tried mutiple colors but it changes about 3 times.   The product coverage is horrible and to even attempt to get medium coverage you use several pumps.  With needing several pumps the bottle doesn't last long about 2 months where other foundation typically last me 6 months at least.   Once its on it has a weird feeling like tacky and made my skin feel itchy,  and sometimes burn.  It has actually made my skib appearance look horrible and has caused flaking a breaking out.   I really tried to love this foundation but i just can't anymore.  I'm going back to Ulta today to get my oldy but goody Clinique.  Lastly,  i will give a separate review on the primer as it's amazing and well worth every penny!

reviews.headline: Not a fan. Doesn't stand up to heat
reviews.comments: I did not like the smell of it at all. I was not aware it smelled like an aromatherapy foundation. It also didn't hold up to the the heat of a kitchen. I will not use again and will go back to Clinique.

reviews.headline: Must have in your makeup bag
reviews.comments: I have been trying for months to find a good foundation that isn't too heavy but goes well with my combination skin. This is by far my favorite foundation and I wore it all day on a sunny day.

reviews.headline: Underrated
reviews.comments: Nothing compares to this for color matching my olive/nuetral skin and it's a comfortable foundation to wear. I see comments about it being drying but I've never had that issue because I always wash, either tone or use an exfoliant pad, then use a quality moisturizer, let it sit then add this foundation with either a blender or a brush. A little goes a long way and it's perfect.

reviews.headline: Would buy again
reviews.comments: good coverage

reviews.headline: VERY drying - Made my skin look old & dull.
reviews.comments: Was shocked to have my own poor experince after reading all the reviews for this. I thought this foundation would be a sure thing, but it made my skin feel so incredibly DRY and looked dull. Yuck!

reviews.headline: Best Color Match Range
reviews.comments:
I used to use Lancome and they changed their formula and it sucks. 
So, I needed something that lasted just as long. 
I work 12-hour shifts at the hospital and I can't even believe my eyes how good the color match is. I wear Neutral Honey.  this makes my skin glow. So glad I found this.

reviews.headline: Will never buy it again
reviews.comments: Come off way too easy

reviews.headline: I would not purchase this again
reviews.comments: It didn't wear  long. It only lasted 4 hrs. The coverage wasn't full coverage.It made my face look dull.

reviews.headline: Smell bad
reviews.comments: I cant leave it on my face for over 5 minutes, so mad Im beyong 30 days for return-cost too much

reviews.headline: Best foundation ever
reviews.comments: I like it so much especially as it is light weight,blends easily, doesn't break me out and stays on longer

reviews.headline: Perfect!
reviews.comments: Perfect match, weightless, and great coverage! So happy to have made this switch!

faceoff_positive.comments:
Offered by Bobbi brown. As a makeup enthusiast, I'm always on the lookout for a foundation that not only provides excellent coverage but also feels light and natural on the skin. Bobbi Brown's new Weightless Skin Foundation has surpassed my expectations in every way, earning a permanent spot in my makeup routine.

Texture and Application:
The first thing I noticed about this foundation is its incredibly lightweight texture. It glides on smoothly and blends effortlessly, providing a seamless finish that feels almost like a second skin. Despite its lightweight feel, the foundation offers buildable coverage, allowing me to customize the level of coverage I need without feeling cakey or heavy.

Coverage and Finish:
Bobbi Brown has truly nailed the balance between coverage and a natural finish with this product. The foundation effectively conceals imperfections, redness, and uneven skin tone while maintaining a fresh, dewy look. It doesn't settle into fine lines or pores, making it ideal for all skin types, including mature skin.

Longevity:
One of the standout features of the Weightless Skin Foundation is its impressive staying power. It lasts all day without oxidizing or fading, even in humid conditions. I was pleasantly surprised to find that it stayed put through long workdays and even a few workouts, all while maintaining its flawless appearance.

Shade Range:
Bobbi Brown has always been known for its inclusive shade range, and this foundation is no exception. With a diverse array of shades that cater to different undertones, finding a perfect match was a breeze. The foundation adapts beautifully to my skin tone, providing a natural and radiant finish.

Skin Benefits:
Beyond its cosmetic benefits, the Weightless Skin Foundation is infused with skin-loving ingredients that provide hydration and nourishment throughout the day. My skin feels comfortable and moisturized, and I appreciate that it doesn't contribute to breakouts or irritation.

faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing

faceoff_negative.comments: I finally went through my bottles of the former formulation, Bobbi Brown Skin Long-Wear Weightless Foundation SPF 15 Golden Honey (W-068). Why did they mess with a great thing? I found the new foundation watery and did not have the same coverage as the previous formula. The only good thing I liked about the foundation is that the color was a spot on match for my skin tone. I'm so disappointed, I had worn BB Skin Long-Wear Weightless Foundation for 10+ years. It stayed on so well during the day. I do prep with Face Base. By the end of the day I was an oily mess, and that never happened with Skin Long-wear Weightless Foundation. Also, the coverage, the previous formula covered past acne scars and discoloration. This new formula does not. I feel so...meh about this foundation. Just didn't wow me like when I first used the BB Skin Long-Wear Weightless Foundation. I think I'll start looking at other brands. It breaks my heart because BB always had my skintone.
faceoff_negative.headline: Not Really Impressed With The New Formula
